# Project log

This repo has a living diary: **`PROJECT_LOG.md`**.

After you complete meaningful work in this project, append to it without being asked:

- **Bug fix** — what broke, why, how we fixed it (with date/time)
- **New feature** — what it does in one plain sentence
- **Demo milestone** — e.g. first successful investigate run
- **Decision** — product or architecture choice and the reason
- **Blocker / break** — if the user steps away or work is stuck

Format for timeline entries:

```markdown
### Day Mon DD Mon YYYY — HH:MM — Short title

**What happened:** ...
**Problem (if any):** ...
**Fix / result:** ...
```

Write in **easy language**. Newest entries go **at the top** of the Timeline section (below "Where we are right now").

Also update **Where we are right now** and check off items in **What's next** when appropriate.

Do not rewrite old entries unless the user asks. Do not duplicate PRODUCT.md — the log is the journal; PRODUCT.md is the product lock (belief evolution / success overturn).
